art rhythm, shortness of breath, or syncope. Ranolazine is contraindicated in patients with liver cirrhosis because of the profound effect on QT prolongation in this population.', 'Metabolism, Synergism', 'Concomitant use of ranolazine and tramadol should generally be avoided.', NULL, NULL, 'Moderate', 'pharmacodynamic');
